<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. A, B Bayesian tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in bold occur in Central America; Scale bar: 2 %." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887869" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.230.103882.figure18>
    dc:description "Figure 18. A-E Muhlenbergia plumbea (Trin.) Hitchc. A habit B ligule C glumes D floret E stamens and lodicules F-L Muhlenbergia utilis (Torr.) Hitchc. F habit G rhizome H ligule I glumes J floret K stamens, pistil, and lodicules. A-E drawn from C. G. Pringle 9581 (US- 396634) F-L drawn from A, S. Hitchcock 5652 (US)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/887886" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

